---
import TechStack from './TechStack';
---

<section id="about" class="min-h-screen flex items-center pt-16 bg-bg-light dark:bg-bg-dark text-text-light dark:text-text-dark">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-20">
      
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <h2 class="text-5xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-center lg:text-left">
          About Me
        </h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6 opacity-80">
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
            I work as a full-stack developer focused on designing and developing complete digital solutions that are scalable, reliable, and well structured. My experience spans across the entire development process, allowing me to transform ideas into functional and efficient web applications. On the front end, I build interfaces that combine performance, usability, and visual consistency, always prioritizing a clean user experience and thoughtful design.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
            On the back end, I develop robust APIs and systems with attention to architecture, data integrity, and long term maintainability. I actively contribute to product evolution by optimizing workflows, improving system quality, and ensuring technical consistency throughout each stage of development. I also have a strong interest in application security, following best practices related to authentication, access control, API protection, and secure system design.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-start">
          <a 
            href="#projects" 
            id="about-cta-button"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-12 py-4 rounded-xl font-medium shadow-md hover:shadow-lg hover:scale-[1.02] transition-all duration-300"
          >
            More information
          </a>
        </div>

        <script>
          const button = document.getElementById('about-cta-button');
          if (button) {
            const updateButtonStyle = () => {
              if (document.documentElement.classList.contains('dark')) {
                button.style.backgroundColor = '#ffffff';
                button.style.color = '#000000';
              } else {
                button.style.backgroundColor = '#000000';
                button.style.color = '#ffffff';
              }
            };
            
            updateButtonStyle();
            const observer = new MutationObserver(updateButtonStyle);
            observer.observe(document.documentElement, { attributes: true, attributeFilter: ['class'] });
          }
        </script>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-5xl lg:text-5xl font-bold mb-10 text-center lg:text-left">
          My Skills
        </h2>
        <TechStack client:load />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>